Montenegrin Second League|Montenegrin Second League]]\n|result12=R\n|class_rules=1) points; 2) goal difference; 3) number of goals scored.<br>The winners of the [[2011\u201312 Montenegrin Cup]], [[FK \u010celik Nik\u0161i\u0107]] (playing in the Montenegrin Second League), will also qualify for the [[2012\u201313 UEFA Europa League#First qualifying round|first qualifying round]] of the UEFA Europa League.\n|update=complete\n|source=[http://www.fscg.co.me/component/option,com_joomleague/Itemid,121/func,showResultsRank/p,1/ fscg.co.me]\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Results==\nThe schedule consisted of three rounds. During the first two rounds, each team played each other once home and away for a total of 22 matches. The pairings of the third round were then set according to the standings after the first two rounds, giving every team a third game against each opponent for a total of 33 games per team.\n\n===First and second round===\n{{#invoke:Sports results|main\n|matches_style=FBR|solid_cell=grey\n|team1=BER|team2=BOK|team3=BUD|team4=DE\u010c|team5=GRB\n|team6=LOV|team7=MLA|team8=MOG|team9=PET|team10=RUD\n|team11=SUT|team12=ZET\n\n|name_BER=[[FK Berane|Berane]]\n|match_BER_BOK=1\u20130\n|match_BER_BUD=0\u20131\n|match_BER_DE\u010c=2\u20130\n|match_BER_GRB=1\u20133\n|match_BER_LOV=2\u20131\n|match_BER_MLA=0\u20131\n|match_BER_MOG=2\u20134\n|match_BER_PET=2\u20132\n|match_BER_RUD=0\u20130\n|match_BER_SUT=1\u20131\n|match_BER_ZET=2\u20133\n\n|name_BOK=[[FK Bokelj|Bokelj]]\n|match_BOK_BER=2\u20130\n|match_BOK_BUD=0\u20131\n|match_BOK_DE\u010c=1\u20133\n|match_BOK_GRB=1\u20130\n|match_BOK_LOV=1\u20131\n|match_BOK_MLA=0\u20133\n|match_BOK_MOG=0\u20133\n|match_BOK_PET=0\u20130\n|match_BOK_RUD=1\u20132\n|match_BOK_SUT=0\u20132\n|match_BOK_ZET=2\u20131\n\n|name_BUD=[[FK Budu\u0107nost Podgorica|Budu\u0107nost Podgorica]]\n|match_BUD_BER=3\u20131\n|match_BUD_BOK=1\u20131\n|match_BUD_DE\u010c=5\u20130\n|match_BUD_GRB=3\u20131\n|match_BUD_LOV=4\u20130\n|match_BUD_MLA=3\u20131\n|match_B